    "num": "02",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">02</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Terminology Clarification</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Defining 'Texican': Origins and Usage</h2><ul><li>'Texican' originally described Mexican residents of Texas</li><li>Term predates 'Texian' and 'Texan'</li><li>Reflects cultural and political identity under Mexican rule</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">'Texican' was used during the Mexican governance of Texas to describe inhabitants of Mexican descent. This term captures the cultural and political realities before Texas independence and statehood. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Mexican family living in Texas in 1825 would identify as Texicans, reflecting their Mexican citizenship and cultural ties.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify which historical period the term 'Texican' best fits and why.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Attributing the term 'Texican' to Anglo settlers or post-independence Texans.</p></div></div>",
