    "eyebrow": "Historical Context",
    "num": "05",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">05</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Context</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texas under Mexican Rule: Political Landscape (1820-1836)</h2><ul><li>Texas was a northern province of Mexico after 1821 independence</li><li>Mexican government encouraged colonization to stabilize the region</li><li>Land grants and empresario contracts attracted settlers</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Following Mexico's independence from Spain, Texas became part of Mexico. The government sought to develop and secure the territory by inviting settlers under regulated land grant programs. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Stephen F. Austin received an empresario grant to bring Anglo settlers to Texas, shaping early colonization patterns.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify key Mexican policies that influenced settlement in Texas.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texas was independent or under U.S. control during this period.</p></div></div>",
