    "eyebrow": "Social Environment",
    "num": "06",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Social Environment</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Life in Mexican Texas: Society and Culture</h2><ul><li>Texicans included Mexican citizens and Tejanos with Spanish heritage</li><li>Settlers lived in small communities with mixed cultural influences</li><li>Interactions with Native American tribes were frequent and complex</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The social fabric of Texas under Mexican rule was diverse, blending Mexican, Spanish, Anglo, and Native American elements, shaping Texican identity and daily life. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican family might celebrate Catholic traditions while engaging in frontier trade with Native tribes.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Describe how cultural diversity influenced Texican communities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Texicans as culturally homogeneous or isolated.</p></div></div>",
