    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Patterns</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Where and How Texicans Settled</h2><ul><li>Texicans established colonies along rivers and fertile lands</li><li>Land grants encouraged agricultural and ranching lifestyles</li><li>Settlements often bordered Native American territories</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Settlement locations were strategic for agriculture, trade, and defense. Texicans adapted frontier lifestyles balancing Mexican traditions and local conditions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The San Antonio area was a key Texican settlement with missions, ranches, and trade routes.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify factors influencing Texican settlement choices.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming settlements were randomly located without strategic considerations.</p></div></div>",
