    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Environment</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Mexican Governance and Texican Relations</h2><ul><li>Texas governed as part of Coahuila y Tejas state</li><li>Mexican laws regulated immigration, land, and slavery</li><li>Tensions grew over enforcement and cultural differences</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Mexican political structures shaped Texican life but also created friction, especially as Anglo immigration increased and cultural norms clashed. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Mexico’s 1830 immigration law restricted further Anglo settlement, causing discontent among Texicans and settlers.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain how Mexican laws affected Texican and settler relations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the role of Mexican law in escalating tensions.</p></div></div>",
