    "num": "15",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">15</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Native American Interactions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Relations with Native American Tribes</h2><ul><li>Texicans had complex relationships with Native tribes, ranging from trade to conflict</li><li>Some tribes allied with Texicans for mutual benefit</li><li>Territorial disputes and raids were common on the frontier</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlers interacted with Native American tribes in multifaceted ways. While trade and alliances existed, competition over land and resources often led to conflicts and raids. These interactions shaped the security and development of Texican colonies. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The Texicans traded cattle and goods with the Comanche tribe but also faced raids that required defensive measures.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Texican-Native American relations influenced settlement security and expansion.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Simplifying Native American relations as solely hostile or friendly without recognizing the nuanced dynamics.</p></div></div>",
