    "eyebrow": "Discussion Prompt",
    "num": "20",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">20</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Discussion Prompt</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">How Did Frontier Life and Cultural Interactions Shape Texican Identity?</h2><ul><li>Consider the roles of isolation, trade, and conflict</li><li>Reflect on the blending of Anglo-American, Mexican, Spanish, and Native influences</li><li>Discuss how identity evolved in response to political and social pressures</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This discussion encourages learners to synthesize knowledge about the complex cultural and social factors that shaped Texican identity on the frontier, fostering critical thinking about hybridity and adaptation. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A learner might argue that Texican identity was a pragmatic blend of cultures shaped by necessity and political realities.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Engage in a group discussion or write a short reflection on the question.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying identity formation or ignoring the role of conflict and cooperation.</p></div></div>",
