    "num": "21",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">21</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice Checkpoint</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Review: Settlement and Cultural Influences</h2><ul><li>Where were major Texican colonies located and why?</li><li>What were key elements of the Texican frontier lifestyle?</li><li>How did cultural influences blend to shape Texican identity?</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This checkpoint reinforces learners’ understanding of Texican settlement patterns, lifestyle, and cultural background through targeted review questions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A learner might summarize that Texican colonies clustered near rivers for agriculture, lived a self-sufficient frontier life, and blended Anglo, Mexican, Spanish, and Native cultures.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Answer these questions in writing or discussion to consolidate learning.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Confusing Texican cultural identity with purely Anglo-American or Mexican identities.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide21\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; as used in early Texas history?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A term for Anglo-American settlers who arrived after Texas independence&quot;,&quot;A name for the original Spanish settlers and their descendants in Texas before independence&quot;,&quot;A nickname for Native American tribes in Texas&quot;,&quot;A term used exclusively for Mexican government officials in Texas&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; historically referred to Spanish settlers and their descendants in Texas prior to independence, distinguishing them from later Anglo settlers.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the cultural background of the Texicans was shaped by their interactions with Anglo-American settlers, Mexican authorities, and Native American tribes.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer should describe the blending of Spanish, Mexican, Anglo-American, and Native American cultural influences, including frontier lifestyle adaptations and political dynamics. It should mention cultural hybridity and the impact of settlement patterns and political tensions.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;The Texicans&#39; cultural background was a blend of Spanish and Mexican heritage influenced by Anglo-American settlers moving into Texas and interactions with Native American tribes. Their frontier lifestyle combined traditions from these groups, shaped by Mexican governance and conflicts leading up to Texas independence.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;The Texicans had a mixed cultural identity influenced by Spanish, Mexican, Anglo, and Native American cultures.&quot;,&quot;Their culture reflected frontier life shaped by diverse interactions and political tensions.&quot;,&quot;Texican identity evolved through blending traditions from settlers and indigenous peoples under Mexican rule.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
