    "eyebrow": "Application",
    "num": "22",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">22</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Knowledge: Analyzing a Texican Settlement Scenario</h2><ul><li>Given a hypothetical frontier settlement location, assess its suitability for Texican colonization</li><li>Consider geography, Native American presence, and cultural factors</li><li>Propose strategies settlers might use to thrive in this environment</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This application exercise challenges learners to apply their understanding of Texican settlement patterns and cultural interactions to a realistic scenario, fostering critical thinking and problem-solving. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A settlement near a river but close to hostile tribes might require strong defenses and trade alliances to succeed.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate the scenario and outline a plan for successful settlement considering all factors.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the complexity of Native American relations or overestimating the ease of settlement.</p></div></div>",
