    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">25</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Exploring Texican Letters: Personal Perspectives</h2><ul><li>Texican letters reveal daily life, hopes, and struggles</li><li>They provide firsthand accounts of settlement challenges</li><li>Letters show cultural blending and identity formation</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Examining letters from Texicans offers authentic insights into their experiences and worldview during early Texas settlement. These documents highlight personal narratives often absent from official histories. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from a Texican settler describes interactions with Native tribes and the hardships of frontier life, illustrating cultural negotiation and survival strategies.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Read an excerpt from a Texican letter and identify key themes about identity and community challenges.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid assuming all Texican letters reflect uniform experiences; individual perspectives vary widely.</p></div></div>",
