    "eyebrow": "Primary Sources",
    "num": "26",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">26</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Official Texican Records: Land Grants and Governance</h2><ul><li>Land grant documents show settlement patterns and legal frameworks</li><li>Governance records reveal Texican interactions with Mexican authorities</li><li>These sources highlight political and social organization</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Official records such as land grants and municipal documents provide concrete evidence of Texican settlement and governance structures under Mexican rule, illustrating legal and political realities. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A land grant issued to a Texican settler outlines the terms of land ownership and obligations, reflecting Mexican colonization policies.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a land grant excerpt to determine how Mexican law influenced Texican settlement rights.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not overlook the political implications embedded in legal language; these documents reflect power dynamics.</p></div></div>",
