    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Legal Documents: Justice and Social Order</h2><ul><li>Court records show dispute resolution and social norms</li><li>Legal documents reflect Texican adaptation of Mexican law</li><li>They reveal community values and conflicts</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Court and legal records from Texican communities illustrate how settlers managed social order and justice, blending Mexican legal traditions with frontier realities. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s17\">[17]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A court case involving land disputes highlights how Texicans negotiated property rights and community standards.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Review a legal case excerpt and identify how Texican society balanced law and local customs.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not assume legal documents always reflect fair or uniform justice; power dynamics influenced outcomes.</p></div></div>",
