    "eyebrow": "Terminology Evolution",
    "num": "30",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">30</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Terminology Evolution</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">From Texican to Texian: Shifting Identities</h2><ul><li>‘Texian’ emerged during the Texas Revolution era</li><li>Term signaled settlers’ identification with independence efforts</li><li>Reflects political and cultural transition</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">‘Texian’ became common among Anglo-American settlers and others supporting Texas independence, marking a shift from Mexican citizenship to a new Texan identity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Revolutionary documents and proclamations refer to ‘Texians’ as participants in the fight for Texas independence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a historical text using ‘Texian’ and discuss its political implications.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not assume ‘Texian’ was universally accepted; some groups retained ‘Texican’ or other identities.</p></div></div>",
