    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">36</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Source Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Interpreting Texican Court Records</h2><ul><li>Identify types of disputes and resolutions</li><li>Understand application of Mexican law in frontier context</li><li>Explore social norms and conflicts</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Court records provide insight into how Texican communities managed conflicts and maintained social order under Mexican legal frameworks. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s17\">[17]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A land dispute case shows negotiation between settlers and application of legal principles to frontier realities.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Examine a court case excerpt and discuss how justice was administered.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not assume legal outcomes were impartial or consistent.</p></div></div>",
