    "eyebrow": "Cultural Practices",
    "num": "38",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">38</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Practices</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Gaps in Understanding Texican Cultural Practices</h2><ul><li>Limited written records on daily life and traditions</li><li>Oral histories are underrepresented in archives</li><li>Cultural hybridity complicates clear categorization</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican cultural practices are difficult to reconstruct fully due to scarce written documentation and the underuse of oral histories, which are crucial for capturing lived experiences and cultural blending (s2, s10). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> For instance, many Texican festivals and rituals were passed down orally and rarely recorded in official documents.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Reflect on how reliance on written sources might bias our view of Texican culture.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking oral traditions and focusing solely on official records.</p></div></div>",
