    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">42</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Review</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Who Were the Texicans? Key Characteristics</h2><ul><li>Texicans were early settlers in Texas with mixed Anglo, Mexican, Spanish, and indigenous heritage</li><li>They lived frontier lifestyles shaped by cultural hybridity</li><li>Their identity evolved through political and social changes in the region</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Summarizing the Texicans’ identity highlights their diverse cultural background and the dynamic nature of their community within early Texas history (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican communities often blended Mexican legal traditions with Anglo-American farming practices.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Summarize in your own words the defining features of the Texicans.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying Texican identity as solely Anglo or Mexican.</p></div></div>",
