    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">44</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Review</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans’ Role in Early Texas History</h2><ul><li>Texicans were active in political movements leading to Texas independence</li><li>They participated in key battles and governance structures</li><li>Their identity influenced and was influenced by shifting political allegiances</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans played a central role in the political and military events that shaped early Texas, reflecting their complex identity and aspirations (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican leaders were instrumental in the Texas Revolution and the establishment of the Republic of Texas.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain how Texican identity affected their political actions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Texicans as passive subjects rather than active agents in history.</p></div></div>",
