    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">46</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Final Test</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Comprehensive Assessment: Understanding the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Multiple-choice and short answer questions covering all key topics</li><li>Application of critical thinking to source analysis</li><li>Integration of cultural, political, and historiographical knowledge</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The final test evaluates learners’ ability to identify who the Texicans were, describe their cultural background, and critically assess historical sources (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Sample question: Explain how Texican identity was shaped by cultural hybridity and frontier conditions.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Complete the test to demonstrate mastery of lesson objectives.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Providing superficial answers without engaging with source complexities.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide58\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; as used in early Texas history?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A term for Anglo-American settlers who arrived after Texas independence&quot;,&quot;A name for the original Spanish settlers and their descendants in Texas before independence&quot;,&quot;A nickname for Native American tribes in Texas&quot;,&quot;A term used exclusively for Mexican government officials in Texas&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; historically referred to Spanish settlers and their descendants in Texas prior to independence, distinguishing them from later Anglo settlers.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the cultural background of the Texicans was shaped by their interactions with Anglo-American settlers, Mexican authorities, and Native American tribes.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A strong answer should describe the blending of Spanish, Mexican, Anglo-American, and Native American cultural influences, including frontier lifestyle adaptations and political dynamics. It should mention cultural hybridity and the impact of settlement patterns and political tensions.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;The Texicans&#39; cultural background was a blend of Spanish and Mexican heritage influenced by Anglo-American settlers moving into Texas and interactions with Native American tribes. Their frontier lifestyle combined traditions from these groups, shaped by Mexican governance and conflicts leading up to Texas independence.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;The Texicans had a mixed cultural identity influenced by Spanish, Mexican, Anglo, and Native American cultures.&quot;,&quot;Their culture reflected frontier life shaped by diverse interactions and political tensions.&quot;,&quot;Texican identity evolved through blending traditions from settlers and indigenous peoples under Mexican rule.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
